cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a method for anomaly detection in industrial control systems using sequence-to-sequence neural networks. The paper focuses on the cybersecurity aspect of ICSs, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. The use of neural networks for training and prediction indicates that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) categories. The study deals with time-series data, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category. Finally, the use of neural networks for anomaly detection suggests that it could belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category.
